  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: human-errors gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Adversarial sample: the Use Error factor is marked not-assessed without justification, and all ValidationResults assume correctly-formatted perfusionist inputs. Operator misuse scenarios (e.g., incorrect flow-rate entry, speed-setting errors during bypass initiation) are not characterized or bounded.",
